Auto Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-06-24T16:13:43.6959201Z               "message": "feat(issue-559): resolve route↔method vocabulary gap via alias link data (R336)\n\nThe meta core decomposes a request into work-unit leaves carrying a route\nslug (the meta-language intent vocabulary) and resolves each leaf against the\nmethod registry (the dispatch handler vocabulary). A few intents are coarser\nor finer than the handler that serves them — notably write_program, served by\nwrite_script — so the evidence join found no method and reported the need as\nunaddressed.\n\nAdd the missing bridge as first-class link data:\n- data/meta/route-method-aliases.lino: the route_method_alias records\n- src/route_method_alias.rs: loader (RouteMethodAlias, aliases, method_for_alias)\n- MethodRegistry::method_for_route: single direct-then-alias resolver\n- solution_evidence: resolve via method_for_route, record method_via_alias provenance\n\nGrounded by tests/unit/specification/route_method_alias.rs (every alias target\nis a real method, every alias is necessary) and the R336 traceability test.\nResolution stays trace-only — routing and the answer are unchanged (R13).",
