Auto Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-06-24T16:13:43.6973257Z               "message": "feat(issue-559): white-box recursive reasoning per work unit (R337)\n\nAttach a human-readable thought to every recursive meta-core step, mirroring\nthe recursion in both directions: the downward thought (what span was observed,\nwhy the unit was decomposed or judged atomic, and which method an atomic leaf\nresolves to via method_for_route) and the upward thought (how the unit's answer\nis composed from its solved children).\n\nThe reasoning is a parallel tree to the work-unit tree, serialized to Links\nNotation and emitted as the trace-only work_unit_reasoning /\nwork_unit_reasoning:steps events, so the white box is inspectable by users and\ndevelopers, not just the predicate. Trace-only (R13): it changes neither\nrouting nor the answer.\n\n- src/meta_reasoning.rs: WorkUnitReasoning, for_unit, to_links_notation,\n  record_work_unit_reasoning; wired into src/meta_core.rs after the registry.\n- recipe grows to nine ordered steps + reasoning meta_functions.\n- example and case-study walk the new artifact; the route<->method gap section\n  is updated to reflect R336 closing it.\n- tests: tests/unit/specification/meta_reasoning.rs (6) and the R337\n  traceability guard; REQUIREMENTS R337 row; changelog fragment.",
