Auto Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-06-24T16:13:43.7000063Z               "message": "feat(issue-559): gated meta self-improvement loop (R340)\n\nThe meta algorithm now reads itself — the recursive-core recipe (the\nalgorithm encoded as Links Notation) against the live record_meta_core\npipeline (the algorithm as code) — and emits the updated recipe as\nlink-encoded output: which meta_function citations to add and which\nstale ones to drop. Gated and proposal-only (default Off proposes\nnothing; never writes the recipe back), so it changes neither routing\nnor the answer (R13/C3).\n\nThe loop caught a real drift on the way in: the pipeline calls\nrecord_solution_evidence but the recipe did not cite it. Adopting that\nfinding (adding fn_record_solution_evidence) makes the checked-in\nsources self-consistent, and a regression test pins that no-op.\n\n- src/meta_self_improvement.rs: SelfImprovementMode, PipelineStage,\n  MetaRecipeProposal, MetaSelfImprovement (from_repo/from_sources/\n  propose), propose_recipe_update\n- data/meta/recursive-core-recipe.lino: cite record_solution_evidence\n- REQUIREMENTS.md: R340 row; intro range R330-R340\n- tests: specification/meta_self_improvement.rs (synthetic drift +\n  live self-consistency), docs traceability row\n- example + case study + raw-data regenerated; changelog fragment",
