Auto Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-06-24T16:13:43.7034815Z               "message": "feat(issue-559): execute the recursive-core recipe as data (R343)\n\nTurn the self-describing recipe from a checked description into a runnable\nprogram. Each trace-recorded meta_step now binds (records field) to the\nrecorder primitive it drives, and src/recipe_interpreter.rs parses the recipe\ninto an ordered RecipeProgram and executes it against the live recorders,\nthreading the intermediate artifacts and honoring the same mode gates as\nrecord_meta_core.\n\nThe headline guarantee is parity proven by execution:\nRecipeProgram::reproduces_pipeline runs the recipe and record_meta_core on\nfresh event logs and the two are identical event-for-event across the full\n3x3x2 recursion/selection/skill mode matrix and three prompt shapes; the\nrecipe's recorder order also equals the live pipeline's stage order. A\nmisordered dependency or unknown binding is a hard error, not silent\ndivergence. Strictly trace-only: changes neither routing nor the answer (R13).\n\n- src/recipe_interpreter.rs: RecipeStep, RecipeProgram, ExecutionTrace,\n  from_lino, from_repo, recorder_sequence, execute, reproduces_pipeline,\n  to_links_notation\n- data/meta/recursive-core-recipe.lino: records bindings on the 9 recorder\n  steps, executability clause, from_lino/execute meta_functions\n- tests/unit/specification/recipe_interpreter.rs: 9 grounding tests\n- REQUIREMENTS.md R343 row; docs case study section; example demo; changelog",
