Auto Release	UNKNOWN STEP	2026-06-24T16:13:43.7047903Z               "message": "feat(issue-559): corpus-wide dispatch-parity certificate (R344)\n\nProve the data-driven method registry is a behavior-preserving drop-in for\nthe hardcoded specialized_handler_name dispatch table across the entire route\nvocabulary the system can emit, not just one prompt's leaves (R339).\n\nsrc/dispatch_parity.rs enumerates the corpus from live data (registry method\nnames, route->method aliases, classifier route slugs, write_program) and\nclassifies each route with the same SelectionAgreement::classify rule (now\npub(crate)). DispatchParity::is_retire_safe is zero contradictions: 63 routes\naudited, 53 agree, 1 alias rescue (write_program->write_script), 9 unresolved,\n0 contradict. Standalone certificate, trace-only (R13).\n\nAdds REQUIREMENTS row R344, traceability test, changelog fragment, example\ndemo, case-study narrative, and refreshed raw-data capture.",
